'''''Blasto''''' is a game released by [[Gremlin Industries|Gremlin]] in 1978. The player controls a [[spacecraft|spaceship]] and must maneuver it through a [[Land mine|mine]] field. The player tries to beat the [[clock]] to destroy all the mines.

Bert Ankrom set the arcade world record on September 8, 2002, with a verified score of 8,730 points.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.twingalaxies.com/game/blasto/arcade|title=Twin Galaxies - Blasto arcade points|access-date=December 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211224191040/https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twingalaxies.com%2Fgame%2Fblasto%2Farcade|archive-date=December 24, 2021|url-status=live|website=[[Twin Galaxies]]}}</ref>

A port for the [[TI-99/4A]] home computer was later released by [[Milton Bradley Company|Milton Bradley]] in the first quarter of 1981.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://4apedia.com/index.php?title=Blasto|title=Blasto - TI/99/4A-Pedia|access-date=December 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027063321/http://4apedia.com/index.php?title=Blasto|archive-date=October 27, 2020|url-status=live|website=4apedia.com}}</ref>

